{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:46:56.496Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Confidence intervals"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are range estimates that quantify uncertainty in statistical estimates by providing a range of plausible values for an unknown population parameter (like mean, proportion, or model accuracy) along with a specified confidence level. Instead of reporting a single point estimate (e.g., \"model accuracy = 85%\"), a confidence interval gives a range (e.g., \"accuracy = 85% ± 2%, or [83%, 87%]\") with 95% confidence, telling you how precise and reliable your estimate is."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Confidence Intervals — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formal definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "100(1-α)% confidence interval"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for parameter θ is an interval [L, U] where:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(L ≤ θ ≤ U) = 1 - α"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = lower bound (calculated from sample)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "U"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = upper bound (calculated from sample)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = true population parameter (fixed but unknown)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1 - α"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = confidence level (e.g., 0.95 for 95% CI)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[aiunderthehood](https://aiunderthehood.com/foundations/statistics/confidence-intervals)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key intuition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Frequentist interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If you repeat the experiment 100 times and compute a 95% CI each time, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "95 of those intervals will contain the true parameter"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NOT what it means"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"There's a 95% probability that the true value is in this specific interval\"."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " The true parameter θ is fixed (not random); the interval bounds vary across samples. The confidence level describes the procedure's reliability, not the probability for a specific interval."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual analogy:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine fishing for a parameter:\n\nTrue value: θ = 100 (fixed, underwater)\n\nSample 1: CI = [95, 105] → Contains θ (caught!)\nSample 2: CI = [102, 110] → Doesn't contain θ (missed!)\nSample 3: CI = [98, 103] → Contains θ (caught!)\n...\nAfter 100 samples with 95% CI: 95 intervals contain θ, 5 don't\n\nThe 95% is about the PROCEDURE, not any single interval [web:249][web:253]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confidence intervals are essential for quantifying uncertainty in ML:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How confidence intervals apply"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model Evaluation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Report accuracy as 85% ± 2% (95% CI) instead of just 85%"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty Quantification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI shows how precise predictions are"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "A/B Testing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI for difference in model performance shows precision of estimate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Safety Validation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI on error rates ensures safety requirements are met with high confidence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "IR Evaluation with LLMs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PPI/CRC methods generate reliable CIs for metrics using LLM annotations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Diffusion Models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CONffusion constructs CIs around each pixel for safe generation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": When reporting GPT-4 accuracy as \"85% (95% CI: [83%, 87%])\", you're saying the true accuracy is plausibly between 83% and 87%, and this method would capture the true value 95% of the time."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to construct confidence intervals"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "General formula:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI = estimate ± margin_of_error"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "estimate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = point estimate (e.g., sample mean Ȳ)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "margin_of_error"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = critical_value × standard_error"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[skool](https://www.skool.com/artificial-intelligence-8395/confidence-intervals-in-machine-learning)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For mean (μ) with known σ:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI = Ȳ ± z_(1-α/2) × (σ / √n)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ȳ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = sample mean\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "σ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = population standard deviation (known)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "n"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = sample size\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "z"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "(1-α/2)"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": " = critical value from Normal distribution (e.g., z = 1.96 for 95% CI)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[geeksforgeeks](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/confidence-intervals-for-machine-learning/)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For mean (μ) with unknown σ (small sample):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI = Ȳ ± t_(α/2, df) × (s / √n)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "s"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = sample standard deviation\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "italic"}], "text": "(α/2, df)"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": " = critical value from t-distribution with df = n-1"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For proportion (p):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI = p̂ ± z_(1-α/2) × √(p̂(1-p̂) / n)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "p̂"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = sample proportion\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "n"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = sample size"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[geeksforgeeks](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/confidence-intervals-for-machine-learning/)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-step examples"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Model accuracy (95% CI)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Measured accuracy over 100 samples: Ȳ = 0.85\nPopulation σ = 0.05 (known)\nn = 100\n95% CI: z = 1.96\n\nMargin of error = 1.96 × (0.05 / √100)\n                = 1.96 × (0.05 / 10)\n                = 1.96 × 0.005\n                = 0.0098\n\nLower = 0.85 - 0.0098 = 0.8402\nUpper = 0.85 + 0.0098 = 0.8598\n\n95% CI = [0.840, 0.860]\n\nInterpretation: True accuracy is between 84.0% and 86.0% with 95% confidence."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Small sample mean (t-distribution)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sample data: [10, 12, 15, 11, 13]\nn = 5 (small sample)\n\nStep 1: Compute sample mean\nȲ = (10 + 12 + 15 + 11 + 13) / 5 = 12.2\n\nStep 2: Compute sample standard deviation\ns = √[((10-12.2)² + (12-12.2)² + ... + (13-12.2)²) / (5-1)]\n  = √[(4.84 + 0.04 + 7.84 + 1.44 + 0.64) / 4]\n  = √(14.8 / 4)\n  = √3.7\n  = 1.92\n\nStep 3: Find t-critical value (95% CI, df = 4)\nt_(0.025, 4) = 2.776 (from t-table)\n\nStep 4: Compute margin of error\nME = 2.776 × (1.92 / √5)\n   = 2.776 × 0.86\n   = 2.39\n\nStep 5: CI\nLower = 12.2 - 2.39 = 9.81\nUpper = 12.2 + 2.39 = 14.59\n\n95% CI = [9.81, 14.59]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confidence interval for mean:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\n\n# Sample data\ndata = np.array([10, 12, 15, 11, 13])\n\n# Point estimate\nmean = np.mean(data)\nstd = np.std(data, ddof=1)  # sample std\nn = len(data)\n\n# 95% CI using t-distribution\nalpha = 0.05\nt_critical = stats.t.ppf(1 - alpha/2, df=n-1)\nmargin_of_error = t_critical * (std / np.sqrt(n))\n\nci_lower = mean - margin_of_error\nci_upper = mean + margin_of_error\n\nprint(f\"Mean: {mean:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"95% CI: [{ci_lower:.2f}, {ci_upper:.2f}]\")\n# Mean: 12.20, 95% CI: [9.81, 14.59]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confidence interval for proportion (model accuracy):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\n\n# 85 correct out of 100\np_hat = 85 / 100  # 0.85\nn = 100\n\n# 95% CI using Normal approximation\nalpha = 0.05\nz_critical = stats.norm.ppf(1 - alpha/2)  # 1.96\nmargin_of_error = z_critical * np.sqrt(p_hat * (1 - p_hat) / n)\n\nci_lower = p_hat - margin_of_error\nci_upper = p_hat + margin_of_error\n\nprint(f\"Accuracy: {p_hat:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"95% CI: [{ci_lower:.3f}, {ci_upper:.3f}]\")\n# Accuracy: 0.85, 95% CI: [0.774, 0.926]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bootstrap confidence interval (no distribution assumption):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Sample data\ndata = np.array([10, 12, 15, 11, 13])\n\n# Bootstrap: repeatedly sample and compute mean\nbootstrap_means = []\nfor i in range(10000):\n    bootstrap_sample = np.random.choice(data, size=len(data), replace=True)\n    bootstrap_means.append(np.mean(bootstrap_sample))\n\n# 95% CI using percentile method\nci_lower = np.percentile(bootstrap_means, 2.5)  # 2.5th percentile\nci_upper = np.percentile(bootstrap_means, 97.5)  # 97.5th percentile\n\nprint(f\"95% Bootstrap CI: [{ci_lower:.2f}, {ci_upper:.2f}]\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confidence Intervals vs. Hypothesis Testing"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Relationship:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A 95% CI includes the null hypothesis value if p ≥ 0.05\nA 95% CI excludes the null hypothesis value if p < 0.05 [web:202][web:206]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Testing if Model A > Model B (H₀: difference = 0)\n- If CI for difference = [0.02, 0.08]: Excludes 0 → p < 0.05 → Reject H₀\n- If CI for difference = [-0.01, 0.05]: Includes 0 → p ≥ 0.05 → Fail to reject H₀"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[stats.ox.ac](https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/~ripley/StatMethods/SM3.pdf)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why CI is better than p-value alone:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "p-value"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confidence Interval"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Precision"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary (significant/not)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shows range of plausible values"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Magnitude"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Doesn't show effect size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shows how large the effect is"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hard to interpret"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Easy (\"true value is between X and Y\")"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confidence intervals provide more information about "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "precision"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of estimate than p-value alone."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes — Pitfalls to avoid"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correction"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "\"95% chance true value is in CI\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI is about the procedure: 95% of such intervals contain θ, not probability for specific interval"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CI includes 0 = no effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CI includes null value → insufficient evidence, not proof of no effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using Normal for small samples"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use t-distribution when n < 30 and σ unknown/12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ignoring sample size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small samples → wider CI; report CI to show precision"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multiple CIs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing many CIs increases false positives; adjust confidence level"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CI = range estimate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Point estimate ± margin of error"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "95% CI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If you repeat experiment 100 times, 95 intervals will contain true parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NOT probability"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"95% of intervals contain θ\" ≠ \"95% chance θ is in this interval\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula for mean (known σ)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CI = Ȳ ± z × (σ/√n)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula for mean (unknown σ)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CI = Ȳ ± t × (s/√n)/12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula for proportion"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CI = p̂ ± z × √(p̂(1-p̂)/n)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CI vs p-value"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CI includes null value if p ≥ 0.05; excludes if p < 0.05"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CI shows precision"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Width indicates uncertainty; narrower = more precise"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model evaluation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Report accuracy as 85% ± 2% (95% CI)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bootstrap CI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use when no distribution assumption (percentile method)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, confidence intervals quantify uncertainty in model predictions, report performance metrics with precision, validate safety requirements, and provide statistical backing for claims about model quality in production."}]}]}}